'''Tsubaki Shrine''' (椿神社, Tsubaki Jinja) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in [[Ōta Ward]], [[Tokyo]]. Though it does not have formal religious corporation status, it is treated as an auxiliary shrine of {{ill|Kamata Hachiman Shrine|ja|蒲田八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which serves as its supervising shrine.

== Overview ==
The foundation date of the shrine is unknown. It is locally referred to as "Dōsojin-sama," suggesting it originally served as a {{ill|Dōsojin|ja|道祖神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (traveler's guardian deity).<ref name="Historic Walk">{{Cite book|author=Yoshiyuki Niikura|title=Ōta Ward Historic Walk (Tokyo Historic Guide 11)|publisher=Gakuseisha|year=1992|pages=82-84}}</ref>

One unique custom associated with the shrine involves wrapping a hemp cord around the neck. When someone suffers from symptoms such as {{ill|whooping cough|ja|百日咳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|asthma|ja|気管支喘息|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, they take a hemp cord hanging in the shrine's hall and tie it around their neck. If they recover, they offer a new hemp cord to the shrine, often alongside incense offerings. This custom reflects the shrine's blend of {{ill|Shinbutsu-shūgō|ja|神仏習合|1=Shinbutsu-shūgō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (syncretism of Shinto and Buddhism), which persists to this day.<ref name="Historic Walk" />

The shrine remains a focal point of local devotion, and in [[1987]] (Shōwa 62), its main building was reconstructed.<ref name="Hachiman Shrine">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kamatahachiman.org/%E3%83%88%E3%83%83%E3%83%97%E3%83%9A%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B8/%E5%85%BC%E5%8B%99%E7%A4%BE%E3%81%AE%E5%BE%A1%E6%A1%88%E5%86%85/%E6%A4%BF%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE/|title=Tsubaki Shrine|publisher=Kamata Hachiman Shrine|accessdate=2023-08-04}}</ref>

== Access ==
* A 7-minute walk from {{ill|Umeyashiki Station|ja|梅屋敷駅 (東京都)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Auxiliary Shrines ==
The following shrines are supervised by {{ill|Kamata Hachiman Shrine|ja|蒲田八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}:
* {{ill|Kamata Hachiman Shrine|ja|蒲田八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (main shrine)
* {{ill|Hibita Shrine|ja|薭田神社|1=Hieta Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Misono Shrine|ja|御園神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Onna-zuka Shrine|ja|女塚神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Kitano Shrine (Ōta Ward Minami-Kamata)|ja|北野神社 (大田区南蒲田)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

