{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q97196664]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:04, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name = Tsubaki Shrine | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = [[File:Tsubaki Jinja (Ota, Tokyo).JPG|250px]] | location = 2-20-11 Kamata, [[Ōta Ward]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]] | coordinates = {{Coord|35|33|53.9|N|139|43|31.4|E|region:JP-13_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | deity = [[Sarutahiko-no-Mikoto]] | Shrine Rank = | Foundation = Unknown | Main hall = | alternate_name = | Annual festival = | Rituals = | Map = Tokyo city }} '''Tsubaki Shrine''' (椿神社, Tsubaki Jinja) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[Ōta Ward]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]]. Though it does not have formal religious corporation status, it is treated as an auxiliary shrine of {{ill|Kamata Hachiman Shrine|ja|蒲田八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamata Hachiman Shrine|qq=}}, which serves as its supervising shrine.
== Overview == The foundation date of the shrine is unknown. It is locally referred to as "Dōsojin-sama," suggesting it originally served as a [[:en:Dōsojin|Dōsojin]] (traveler's guardian deity).<ref name="Historic Walk">{{Cite book|author=Yoshiyuki Niikura|title=Ōta Ward Historic Walk (Tokyo Historic Guide 11)|publisher=Gakuseisha|year=1992|pages=82-84}}</ref>
One unique custom associated with the shrine involves wrapping a hemp cord around the neck. When someone suffers from symptoms such as [[:en:Whooping cough|whooping cough]] or [[:en:Asthma|asthma]], they take a hemp cord hanging in the shrine's hall and tie it around their neck. If they recover, they offer a new hemp cord to the shrine, often alongside incense offerings. This custom reflects the shrine's blend of [[:en:Shinbutsu-shūgō|Shinbutsu-shūgō]] (syncretism of Shinto and Buddhism), which persists to this day.<ref name="Historic Walk" />
The shrine remains a focal point of local devotion, and in [[:en:1987|1987]] (Shōwa 62), its main building was reconstructed.<ref name="Hachiman Shrine">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kamatahachiman.org/%E3%83%88%E3%83%83%E3%83%97%E3%83%9A%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B8/%E5%85%BC%E5%8B%99%E7%A4%BE%E3%81%AE%E5%BE%A1%E6%A1%88%E5%86%85/%E6%A4%BF%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE/|title=Tsubaki Shrine|publisher=Kamata Hachiman Shrine|accessdate=2023-08-04}}</ref>
== Access == * A 7-minute walk from [[:en:Umeyashiki Station (Tokyo)|Umeyashiki Station]].
== Auxiliary Shrines == The following shrines are supervised by {{ill|Kamata Hachiman Shrine|ja|蒲田八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamata Hachiman Shrine|qq=}}: * {{ill|Kamata Hachiman Shrine|ja|蒲田八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamata Hachiman Shrine|qq=}} (main shrine) * {{ill|Hibita Shrine|ja|薭田神社|1=Hieta Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hibita Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Hieta Shrine|qq=}} * {{ill|Misono Shrine|ja|御園神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Misono Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * {{ill|Onna-zuka Shrine|ja|女塚神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onna-zuka Shrine|qq=}} * {{ill|Kitano Shrine (Ōta Ward Minami-Kamata)|ja|北野神社 (大田区南蒲田)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitano Shrine (Ōta Ward Minami-Kamata)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
